5 increased public, nonprofit and private sector investment and work to enhance the quality
6 of life for all by assisting local governments and nonprofit organizations to plan and
7 implement comprehensive community planning and development strategies.
8 Sec. 2. 5 MRSA §13055, sub-§1, ¶F, as amended by PL 2003, c. 673, Pt. M, §2,
9 is further amended to read:
10 F. The Office of Community Development; and
